            <p><strong>Discoverer:</strong> Akiyoshi Kitaoka (2004)</p>
            <p>Kitaoka developed the Moving Circles illusion during his research into peripheral drift. By arranging shaded blocks in concentric rings, he showed that saccadic eye movements trigger rapid orientation shifts in visual area MT/V5, causing the circles to spin.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

